
class A {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("In A Show")
    }
}

/*

class B extends A {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("In B Show")
    }
}

*/


public class anonymous {
    public static void main(String[] ar) {

        A obj = new A() {
            System.out.println("In new Show")
        };
        // Inner class since we don't have a name It is called Anonymous class

        obj.show();

    }
}


The only purpose of this class B was to extend or to extend a class to override the method, and maybe it will beused only once.